on the Android TV platform.

00:28:01.060 --> 00:28:04.230
So as I said, we are a
video centric application,

00:28:04.230 --> 00:28:08.690
and we needed to build
upon a great player.

00:28:08.690 --> 00:28:15.430
And we chose to use ExoPlayer,
and I will tell you why.

00:28:15.430 --> 00:28:18.810
So it's the heart of the
experience of our services,

00:28:18.810 --> 00:28:23.870
and we needed to handle
many technologies

00:28:23.870 --> 00:28:25.810
inside the application.

00:28:25.810 --> 00:28:27.680
And as you can
see on this slide,

00:28:27.680 --> 00:28:31.770
ExoPlayer handles many, many
features and capabilities,

00:28:31.770 --> 00:28:37.050
from the management of DRM,
timelines, media composition,

00:28:37.050 --> 00:28:40.710
the support of the standards
of the adaptive streamings.

00:28:40.710 --> 00:28:43.100
There is a lot of
containers available.

00:28:43.100 --> 00:28:46.830
There is a lot of
captioning technologies.

00:28:46.830 --> 00:28:51.540
And also, ExoPlayer
gives you nice extensions

00:28:51.540 --> 00:28:53.790
to make your work easier--

00:28:53.790 --> 00:29:01.800
for example, MediaSession to
plug Assistant to the player--

00:29:01.800 --> 00:29:04.570
and some other one.

00:29:04.570 --> 00:29:07.500
So here are some
highlights of what

00:29:07.500 --> 00:29:09.840
we have used inside myCanal.

00:29:09.840 --> 00:29:13.740
So it makes sense
to use ExoPlayer

00:29:13.740 --> 00:29:16.410
inside the application.

00:29:16.410 --> 00:29:23.360
So I will describe four use
cases of the use of ExoPlayer.

00:29:23.360 --> 00:29:28.260
So to start off, media
sources is the entry point

00:29:28.260 --> 00:29:30.000
of your video playback.

00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:34.870
And it will handle all the
transport streams you need.

00:29:34.870 --> 00:29:40.440
In myCanal, we used dash
media sources, [INAUDIBLE]

00:29:40.440 --> 00:29:44.490
sources and HLS media sources.

00:29:44.490 --> 00:29:49.590
So each media sources have
a factory with ExoPlayer,

00:29:49.590 --> 00:29:53.280
and it's really easy
to instantiate them.

00:29:53.280 --> 00:29:56.992
And everything is rooted
with the URI of the manifest

00:29:56.992 --> 00:29:57.700
you want to play.

00:30:00.920 --> 00:30:03.230
The factories of the media
sources from ExoPlayer

00:30:03.230 --> 00:30:07.280
is very be powerful because
you can customize it.

00:30:07.280 --> 00:30:11.240
For example, you may want to
have a custom manifest parser

00:30:11.240 --> 00:30:14.510
to handle the feature
that is not handled

00:30:14.510 --> 00:30:17.330
by default by ExoPlayer.

00:30:17.330 --> 00:30:22.910
You can also adjust your
position of your live streams

00:30:22.910 --> 00:30:26.170
on the live TV channels.

00:30:26.170 --> 00:30:31.370
And you have also a load error
policy that you can customize.

00:30:31.370 --> 00:30:35.930
And here it's a great
feature to handle the load

00:30:35.930 --> 00:30:39.000
errors that you may encounter
during your playback.

00:30:39.000 --> 00:30:41.840
For example, your
manifest can describe

00:30:41.840 --> 00:30:44.570
video chunks that
are not completely

00:30:44.570 --> 00:30:46.760
available on your server.

00:30:46.760 --> 00:30:51.290
And you may get, for
example, some 412 HTTP error.

00:30:51.290 --> 00:30:56.370
And you don't want to make your
playback showing some errors,

00:30:56.370 --> 00:30:59.810
so you have to keep in
mind you may need to retry

00:30:59.810 --> 00:31:01.640
the loading of your chunks.

00:31:01.640 --> 00:31:06.700
So customizing your load error
policy solves this problem.

00:31:10.220 --> 00:31:12.960
OK, one other powerful
feature of ExoPlayer

00:31:12.960 --> 00:31:16.650
is media composition and the
interactive media ad extension

00:31:16.650 --> 00:31:22.050
from ExoPlayer use it
and it's really useful

00:31:22.050 --> 00:31:26.790
to concatenate your content
with the ads and video

00:31:26.790 --> 00:31:29.438
content in a single timeline.

00:31:32.610 --> 00:31:35.460
How you use the IMA extension.

00:31:35.460 --> 00:31:39.240
Of course you need the player.

00:31:39.240 --> 00:31:41.340
And also you have to
[INAUDIBLE] IMA Ads

00:31:41.340 --> 00:31:48.000
Loader, where you will put the
vast ads URI needed to retrieve

00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:50.190
all the ad's content.

00:31:50.190 --> 00:31:55.140
And also all the ad's
impression you have to handle

00:31:55.140 --> 00:31:57.450
gave to the IMA ads and
all the other player

00:31:57.450 --> 00:32:00.960
because during the playback,
the IMA ads extension

00:32:00.960 --> 00:32:06.550
will handle all the
ad's impression for you.

00:32:06.550 --> 00:32:11.790
Then the build media source,
the content you want to play.

00:32:11.790 --> 00:32:16.350
And next, just instantiate
your ad media source

00:32:16.350 --> 00:32:20.490
and give it to it your
content media source.

00:32:20.490 --> 00:32:22.960
And also you need
to give it to it

00:32:22.960 --> 00:32:27.420
player view because the
IMA ad extension will

00:32:27.420 --> 00:32:30.690
provide for you the
interactive URI for your ads.

00:32:33.270 --> 00:32:36.090
Prepare your player and
you're ready to have

00:32:36.090 --> 00:32:43.160
a nice playback of
[INAUDIBLE] inside your video.

00:32:43.160 --> 00:32:45.660
And everything is
handled nicely.

00:32:45.660 --> 00:32:48.090
You will not have
any buffering time

00:32:48.090 --> 00:32:50.760
between the transition
of each videos thanks

00:32:50.760 --> 00:32:52.490
to some magic of
ExoPlayer caching.

00:32:55.920 --> 00:32:58.810
OK, let's talk about DRM.

00:32:58.810 --> 00:33:03.590
Android TV platform supports
the two main DRM agents

00:33:03.590 --> 00:33:07.710
that the content
owners industry trusts.

00:33:07.710 --> 00:33:11.290
It's Google Widevine
and Microsoft PlayReady.

00:33:11.290 --> 00:33:13.910
And thanks to these
two DRM agent,

00:33:13.910 --> 00:33:16.060
we are able to
provide 4K contents.

00:33:18.760 --> 00:33:23.550
ExoPlayer gives you great
tools to manage DRMs.

00:33:23.550 --> 00:33:27.840
So you have a
media DRM interface

00:33:27.840 --> 00:33:31.440
which is exposed by ExoPlayer.

00:33:31.440 --> 00:33:34.620
And you have a callback to
execute the key request, which

00:33:34.620 --> 00:33:39.030
would be triggered by
the DRM session which

00:33:39.030 --> 00:33:43.220
is in the work during
the video decoding.

00:33:43.220 --> 00:33:47.880
And when it's triggered,
you just have to route which

00:33:47.880 --> 00:33:51.360
of the two DRM [INAUDIBLE]
for example, if you

00:33:51.360 --> 00:33:53.580
get a Widevine unique idea.

00:33:53.580 --> 00:33:57.840
You may want to request your
Widevine license server.

00:33:57.840 --> 00:33:59.930
And the same thing
for the PlayReady one.

00:33:59.930 --> 00:34:03.060
You may want to
root your license

00:34:03.060 --> 00:34:05.580
request to the good server.

00:34:05.580 --> 00:34:07.140
Depending on the
scenario, you may

00:34:07.140 --> 00:34:10.565
want to use one or
another DRM arrangement.

00:34:10.565 --> 00:34:11.190
It's up to you.

00:34:13.739 --> 00:34:16.469
So how do we start the
playback with their DRM?

00:34:16.469 --> 00:34:20.960
So as you saw, we
need our DRM callback.

00:34:20.960 --> 00:34:23.840
Then we have to inject it
to a DRM session manager.

00:34:23.840 --> 00:34:28.690
The DRM session manager will
handle all the DRM session

00:34:28.690 --> 00:34:32.810
that's the playback we need and
will handle all the requests

00:34:32.810 --> 00:34:34.290
of license you need.

00:34:37.460 --> 00:34:39.980
Instantiate your
player and inject it

00:34:39.980 --> 00:34:43.820
in the context of ExoPlayer.

00:34:43.820 --> 00:34:44.719
And that's it.

00:34:44.719 --> 00:34:46.760
Your playback is ready.

00:34:46.760 --> 00:34:49.639
If you want to find out
more about ExoPlayer,

00:34:49.639 --> 00:34:51.010
just follow this link.

00:34:51.010 --> 00:34:55.489
And I'd recommend you to watch
IU17 session of the ExoPlayer

00:34:55.489 --> 00:34:58.700
player, where all the
architecture is really

00:34:58.700 --> 00:34:59.913
well described.

00:35:03.090 --> 00:35:06.370
OK, in myCanal, we
have also embraced

00:35:06.370 --> 00:35:09.610
all the features the Android
TV platform offers to us.

