00:36:16.000 --> 00:36:19.580
We use it to launch
any playback we want.

00:36:19.580 --> 00:36:22.870
For example, if we want to watch
the newest movies on myCanal,

00:36:22.870 --> 00:36:26.650
we just have to ask
Assistant, and we play it

00:36:26.650 --> 00:36:27.790
automatically for you.

00:36:30.590 --> 00:36:32.410
But one of the
powerful feature is

00:36:32.410 --> 00:36:34.690
the combination of
the power of Assistant

00:36:34.690 --> 00:36:37.400
and our live TV streams.

00:36:37.400 --> 00:36:40.390
As I said earlier, we have
the StartOver feature.

00:36:40.390 --> 00:36:42.670
And for any live TV
channels on myCanal,

00:36:42.670 --> 00:36:45.160
we can seek into the
past up to eight hours.

00:36:45.160 --> 00:36:47.680
That means we can ask
the Assistant to start

00:36:47.680 --> 00:36:50.740
from the beginning of
any content we want.

00:36:50.740 --> 00:36:55.840
And if you have your great TV
shows, which is already on air

00:36:55.840 --> 00:36:58.290
you can ask Assistant to
start from the beginning.

00:36:58.290 --> 00:37:00.340
Or you may want also
to ask Assistant

00:37:00.340 --> 00:37:03.670
to bring back to
the first episode,

00:37:03.670 --> 00:37:04.950
in this case, if you want.

00:37:09.500 --> 00:37:10.620
That's not it.

00:37:10.620 --> 00:37:14.510
We wanted to push the Android
TV platform to it's limits.

00:37:14.510 --> 00:37:21.380
And I will show you two great
feature we did inside myCanal.

00:37:21.380 --> 00:37:25.600
The first one is what
